## help
- label: agent-store documented subcommands, aliases, and hook subcommands treat -h and --help as read-only help: each exits 0, prints command-specific usage, and does not create, update, delete, link, unlink, or run Hooks
  id: x3h
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_help.sh subcommand_help_is_read_only
  tags: [implemented]

# domain
- label: a Store is a project-local SQLite-backed database under .agent-store
  command: bash tests/facts/store_schema_migrations.sh store_is_project_local
  tags: [implemented]
- label: a Record is a stored item with a generated 6-8 character random hash ID, a kind, and arbitrary named Fields
  id: 6hu
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_records.sh json_output
  tags: [implemented]
- label: a Field is a key-value attribute attached to a Record
  id: ypj
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_records.sh field_empty_null_unset_semantics
  tags: [implemented]
- label: a Query is a boolean expression over Record kind, Fields, typed comparisons, parentheses, and Link predicates
  id: wqi
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_records.sh query_boolean_syntax && bash tests/facts/cli_records.sh query_typed_values && bash tests/facts/cli_links.sh find_filters_links
  tags: [implemented]
- label: a Hook is a stored automation rule with a generated 6-8 character random hash ID, supported Store Event name, optional Query condition text, Bash command, and created_at timestamp
  id: u79
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_hooks.sh hook_add_stores_metadata
  tags: [implemented]
- label: each successful create, set, unset, rm, link, and unlink mutation writes one Store Event with event_type equal to the mutation name, record_id set to the affected Record ID, and link/unlink using the source Record as the affected Record
  id: rc5
  command: bash tests/facts/store_events.sh mutation_events
  tags: [implemented]
- label: a Hook Run persists one Hook invocation result with Hook ID, Store Event name, affected Record ID, exit status, stdout summary, stderr summary, and creation timestamp
  id: ra7
  command: CARGO_TARGET_DIR=target/facts-ra7 cargo test hook_runs_persist_invocation_results
  tags: [implemented]
- label: a Quick Context is an at-most-8192-byte Store summary that reports aggregate counts, Field names, status counts, and due/start windows while omitting Record IDs, Hook IDs, Hook queries, Hook commands, and other Field values
  id: w8e
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_context.sh ctx_domain_summary_contract
  tags: [implemented]
- label: a Link is a stored directional typed relation from one source Record to one target Record
  id: cw3
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_links.sh links_lists_deterministically
  tags: [implemented]
- label: one Link table shape represents one-to-one, one-to-many, and many-to-many relations without per-kind schema changes
  command: bash tests/facts/store_schema_migrations.sh record_links_cardinality_shape
  tags: [implemented]

