# architecture
- label: callers can open a Store for a chosen project root and exercise record, query, link, and Quick Context behavior through Store and Query APIs without naming the SQLite database path or schema tables
  id: 5xe
  command: CARGO_TARGET_DIR=target/facts-5xe cargo test --test persistence_interface persistence_interface_allows_behavior_tests_without_sqlite_layout
  tags: [implemented]

# decisions

## open
- token-efficient agent usage uses generic CRUD commands plus short aliases instead of type-specific task or calendar subcommands @draft
- the Rust SQLite crate and async model are chosen based on simple CLI correctness, migration support, and testability rather than background service throughput @draft

# hooks
- label: Hooks without Query conditions run only after a triggering Store mutation succeeds and commits, can read the committed Record through a nested agent-store command, do not run for failed mutations, and persist one Hook Run per invocation
  id: w5s
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_hooks.sh hooks_run_after_commit
  tags: [implemented]
- label: Hook Query conditions are evaluated with the same boolean kind-and-Field Query language as agent-store find; matching Hooks run and persist Hook Runs, while non-matching Hooks are skipped without Hook Runs
  id: mlq
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_hooks.sh hook_query_filters_records
  tags: [implemented]
- label: create, set, and unset Hooks evaluate their Query against the Record after the change; rm Hooks evaluate against the pre-delete Record snapshot
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_hooks.sh hook_query_uses_mutation_snapshot
  tags: [implemented]
- label: Hook Bash commands receive the affected Record snapshot on stdin as one default-format Record line
