  command: bash tests/facts/cli_hooks.sh hook_failure_reports_details
  tags: [implemented]
- label: Matching Hooks for plain create, set, unset, rm, link, and unlink mutations run sequentially after the triggering mutation commits; earlier successful Hook Runs persist, the first failing or timed-out Hook Run persists and makes the CLI exit non-zero with empty stdout and useful stderr, later matching Hooks do not run, the Store mutation remains committed, and each Bash command starts in the project root with the default 30-second timeout
  id: 4as
  command: bash tests/facts/cli_hooks.sh hooks_run_sequentially_from_project_root_with_timeout
  tags: [implemented]
- label: Hook Bash commands for create, set, unset, and rm receive AGENT_STORE_EVENT, AGENT_STORE_ID, and AGENT_STORE_KIND matching the affected Record snapshot
